OL,3,CThursday's elections could be
OL,4,C'Starmageddon' for PM, Stephen Flynn
OL,5,Cwarns
OL,7,FAdding that the Labour leader had been
OL,8,F"a disappointment from day one"
OL,9,Faccusing him of "betraying" women
OL,10,Fcampaigning over state pension
OL,11,Finequality, and hitting out at the
OL,12,Frise in employer national insurance
OL,13,Fcontributions.
OL,15,FMr Flynn went on to accuse Sir Keir of
OL,16,F"breaking his promises" over the
OL,17,FGrangemouth oil refinery, "destroying
OL,18,Fthousands of Scottish energy jobs, and
OL,19,Ffailing to act as the cost of living
OL,20,Fsoars on his watch".
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@_O]qD@QOUqD@[O]xD@AOUxD@WO]yD@
OL,26,A[OU|D@SO]
